Rating: 4
This is such a great easy recipe for a side salad. I did a couple things differently by accident...I added a table spoon of dijon so added more honey then too. It was still a fantastic dressing that I would use for all sorts of things. My peppers were out of a jar which might have added to the tang...I also added crumbled goat cheese which added a very nice creamyness. I would also add fresh slices of red pepper and red onion...I think that would add a nice crunch/crispness.

