Rating: 2
I love spinach and roasted red peppers, but with the honey-balsamic dressing, I found the whole thing too sweet for a dinner salad. Balsamic vinegar already has a sweetness to it, then with the honey...even when I added more Dijon - that didn't cut the sweetness. I added more salt, still too sweet. But the peppers and spinach were a nice combination.

