Rating: 4
I took the suggestion from the cook from Pittsburgh and added roasted eggplant, zucchini and feta cheese. I accidently marinated the veggies in the dressing overnight. When I realize this I drained the veggies, saving the dressing, and tossed them with the spinach. It turned out great anyways. There was enough dressing on the veggies that it got on the spinach

Rating: 4
I added roasted/grilled eggplant, zucchini, fennel, and turnips to the roasted red and yellow peppers. I placed the spinach in the bottom of the bowl and pinwheeled the veggies around on top. In the middle I added a mound of feta cheese. It was the hit of the party. I was the only person to not have left-overs in their bowl!